---
import Base from "../layouts/Base.astro";
import Feature from "../components/Feature.astro";
---

<Base title="Mac Storage Clear">
  <section class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-6 pt-20 pb-16">
    <div class="max-w-3xl">
      <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-semibold tracking-tight leading-[1.1]">
        See what's eating your Mac's storage. Clear it with confidence.
      </h1>
      <p class="mt-6 text-lg text-ink/70 leading-relaxed">
        Apple Silicon-native disk visualizer. Find duplicate dev directories, manage screenshots,
        identify large files and stale projects. Quarantine first, hard-delete when you're sure.
        Open source. No telemetry. Ever.
      </p>
      <div class="mt-10 flex flex-wrap gap-4 items-center">
        <a
          href="#"
          aria-disabled="true"
          class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-5 py-3 bg-ink text-paper rounded-lg font-medium opacity-60 cursor-not-allowed"
        >
          Download on the Mac App Store · coming soon
        </a>
        <a
          href="https://github.com/aanya-send-help/mac-storage-clear"
          class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-5 py-3 border border-ink/15 rounded-lg font-medium hover:border-ink/40"
          rel="noopener"
        >
          Build from source →
        </a>
      </div>
      <p class="mt-4 text-sm text-ink/50">
        $9.99 one-time on the App Store. Free if you build it yourself. Same app either way.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section id="features" class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-6 py-16 border-t border-black/5">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold tracking-tight">What it does</h2>
    <div class="mt-8 grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
      <Feature
        title="Treemap visualization"
        body="Interactive map of every directory under your home and Library. Click to drill in, color-coded by category."
      />
      <Feature
        title="Duplicate dev directories"
        body="Finds node_modules, .venv, target, DerivedData, and __pycache__ across stale projects. Knows the difference between local artifacts and shared package caches."
      />
      <Feature
        title="Screenshot manager"
        body="Gallery view for every Screen Shot on your desktop. Bulk delete or one-by-one with keyboard shortcuts."
      />
      <Feature
        title="Stale-project detection"
        body="Cross-references git log, lockfile age, and remote sync to surface projects you haven't touched in 90+ days that are safe to clean."
      />
      <Feature
        title="APFS clone aware"
        body="Detects copy-on-write clones so we never inflate your potential savings with bytes that aren't actually duplicated."
      />
      <Feature
        title="Quarantine first"
        body="Automated cleanups move files to a 7-day quarantine before any unlink. Manual selections hard-delete by default — your call."
      />
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-6 py-16 border-t border-black/5">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold tracking-tight">Open source by default</h2>
    <div class="mt-6 text-ink/70 leading-relaxed max-w-3xl space-y-4">
      <p>
        Mac Storage Clear is MIT licensed and developed in the open at <a
          href="https://github.com/aanya-send-help/mac-storage-clear"
          class="underline decoration-rose-400 underline-offset-4 hover:text-ink"
          rel="noopener">github.com/aanya-send-help/mac-storage-clear</a
        >.
      </p>
      <p>
        Buying on the App Store gets you signed, notarized binaries, automatic updates, and family
        sharing. Building from source gets you the same app for free, plus the ability to scan
        across multiple user accounts via a privileged helper (which the App Store sandbox
        prohibits).
      </p>
      <p>Either way, all your data stays on your machine. Always.</p>
    </div>
  </section>
</Base>
